INSTALLING MEDUSA:

All programs were written in C++, on a Unix system.  However, user
interface is minimal, so programs should be easily portable to any
platform.

To compile on a Unix system, simply put all source code in a
directory, together with the Makefile, and type "make all". To remove all
executables (if you've changed something and want to recompile), type
"make clean".

If you do make a windows or mac version, please notify us at
math@math.cornell.edu


Programs were written by:  Christian Henriksen, David Farris, and Kuan Ju
Liu at Cornell University in Summer 1998.
